        &raquo;</div>
                        
<div class="txt-block" id="name-bio-text">
        <div class="name-trivia-bio-text">
                      <div class="inline" itemprop="description">
Rajkumar Hirani was born on November 20, 1962 in Nagpur, Maharashtra, India. He is a writer and editor, known for <a href="/title/tt1187043?ref_=nm_ov_bio_lk1">3 Idiots</a> (2009), <a href="/title/tt2338151?ref_=nm_ov_bio_lk2">PK</a> (2014) and <a href="/title/tt0374887?ref_=nm_ov_bio_lk3">Munna Bhai M.B.B.S.</a> (2003).            <span class="see-more inline nobr-only">
                    <a href="/name/nm0386246/bio?ref_=nm_ov_bio_sm"
>See full bio</a> &raquo;
            </span>
</div>        </div>
</div>

                        
    <div id="name-born-info" class="txt-block">
        <h4 class="inline">Born:</h4> 
   
  <time datetime="1962-11-20" itemprop="birthDate">
<a href="/search/name?birth_monthday=11-20&refine=birth_monthday&ref_=nm_ov_bth_monthday"
>November 20</a>, 
     
<a href="/search/name?birth_year=1962&ref_=nm_ov_bth_year"
>1962</a>    
  </time>
            in
            <a href="/search/name?birth_place=Nagpur,+Maharashtra,+India&ref_=nm_ov_bth_place"
>Nagpur, Maharashtra, India</a>
    </div>

                        
                        
